Find command is used to search and locate the files and directories based on the conditions.

1. Find Files using Name in the Current Directory

# find . -name text.txt

2. Find Files in absolute path [ /tmp ]

# find /tmp -name text.txt

3. Find Files using Name and Ignore Case

# find /tmp -iname Text.txt

4. Find Directories Using Name

# find / -type d -name demo

5. Find all PHP Files

# find /tmp -type f -name Test.php

6. Find all Files ends with ".php"

# find /tmp -type f -name "*.php"

7. Find Files with 777 permision

# find / -type f -perm 0777 -print

8. Find Files without 777 permission

# find / -type f ! -prem 777 -print

9. Find Read Only Files

# find / -type f -perm /u=r

10. Find Executable Files

# find / -perm /a=x

11. Find Files with 777 Permissions and Chmod to 644

# find / -type f -perm 0777 -print -exec chmod 644 {} \;

12. Find Directories with 777 Permissions and Chmod to 755

# find / -type d -prem 0777 -print -exec chmod 755 {} \;

13. Find and Remove Single File

# find /tmp -type f -name "text.txt" -exec rm -rf {} \;

14. Find and Remove files ending with "*.txt"

# find / -type f -name "*.txt" -exec rm -rf {} \;

15. Find all Empty Files

# find /tmp -type f -empty

16. Find all Empty Directories

# find /tmp -type d -empty

17. Find all Hidden Files

# find /tmp -type f -name ".*"

